<p>Touloun is a great pleasure resort of the French people &amp; well it might be for it is a lovely looking place without a doubt about it. As we entered Touloun the band played &amp; the sun shone brilliantly &amp; all took it as a happy omen, for our first introduction to France.<br/>That night we anchored in the harbour, &amp; a good concert was held on board, next morning we set sail for Marseilles, &amp; during this run some dirty sneaking thief stole my tunic &amp; contents out of my cabins, he got a fair haul altogether, &pound; 2.10 in money a splendid fountain pen, pocket</p>
